## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Dense, solid, firm, unyielding on soft touch.
    - Feedback: Direct and clear. You know exactly where on the racket you hit the ball.
    - Hold vs. Release: Massive hold (dwell) due to the sticky surface, followed by a delayed, powerful release once the sponge kicks in.
    - Dwell Time: Very long on brushing shots; moderate on flat drives.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a muted thud on soft shots and a sharp, cracking smack on high-impact power loops. It lacks the high-pitched metallic click of softer, older-generation tensors.

